  "text": "[12] The air in the stainless steel canisters was analyzed by gas chromatography (GC) for CO 2 , NMHCs, chlorocarbons, CFCs, and aromatic compounds (see [CITATION_1] for details). A flame ionization detector (FID) was used for NMHCs and aromatic compounds, and an electron capture detector (ECD) for chlorocarbons (including CH 3 Cl) and CFCs. The precision of the analyses (1s) was 2% for CFC-12 and methyl chloride and 5% for the NMHCs. The detection limits for these gases are 15 ppt.",
